      </prefercite>
      <scopecontent id="aspace_4b415b67e20d686f9986f16450b3af49">
         <head>Scope and Contents</head>
         <p>The papers of Ephraim B. Bishop relate to various aspects of commerce in the southern United States from 1832 to 1887. Included are business correspondence, contracts and agreements, receipts, notes, bills, Confederate States exchange certificates, and other papers dealing with the collection of debts and the sale of cattle, goods, and slaves from South Carolina to Texas. Bishop held a patent for river dredging machinery, and a segment of the paper concerns his marketing of this equipment after the Civil War. Also in the papers are Bishop's post-war loyalty oaths and voter registration.</p>
         <p>These papers were purchased from Anna A. Prince in 1968.</p>  
      </scopecontent>
  
